Gotta catch 'em all!

00:03:08.488 --> 00:03:09.523
CLEMBOT: I found the right code!

00:03:14.528 --> 00:03:15.862
TEAM FLARE GRUNT : Who's there?!

00:03:15.862 --> 00:03:18.165
CLEMONT: I'm the
Lumiose Gym Leader, Clemont!

00:03:18.165 --> 00:03:20.567
CLEMBOT: And I'm the
substitute Gym Leader, Clembot!

00:03:20.567 --> 00:03:21.802
CLEMONT: What do you see?

00:03:21.802 --> 00:03:23.136
CLEMBOT: I'm scanning now.

00:03:25.906 --> 00:03:28.575
CLEMBOT: There are
three of them, one further back.

00:03:28.575 --> 00:03:30.811
CLEMBOT: I detect the very
same elements in their device as

00:03:30.811 --> 00:03:32.979
contained within
the red Zygarde.

00:03:32.979 --> 00:03:34.081
CLEMONT:
Maybe it's their control system.

00:03:35.749 --> 00:03:37.818
CLEMBOT: It is possible that I
could infiltrate their system

00:03:37.818 --> 00:03:39.019
and stop it from functioning.

00:03:39.019 --> 00:03:40.220
CLEMONT: Good!

00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:41.755
CLEMONT: Use Electric Terrain!

00:03:41.755 --> 00:03:44.658
LUXRAY: [ELECTRIC TERRAIN MOVE]

00:03:48.228 --> 00:03:49.362
CLEMONT:
Clembot, now's your chance!

00:03:49.362 --> 00:03:51.264
CLEMBOT: Right!

00:03:51.264 --> 00:03:52.666
XEROSIC: What's all the ruckus?

00:03:55.202 --> 00:03:59.005
XEROSIC: Well, well. I see
we have some uninvited guests.

00:04:00.507 --> 00:04:01.708
XEROSIC: What are
Byrony and the others doing?

00:04:03.343 --> 00:04:04.978
CLEMONT: You're controlling
Zygarde

00:04:04.978 --> 00:04:06.513
with that control
system, aren't you?

00:04:06.513 --> 00:04:09.783
XEROSIC: True! It's one
of my greatest inventions!

00:04:09.783 --> 00:04:12.252
CLEMONT: Things that
control Pokémon, destroy cities,

00:04:12.252 --> 00:04:13.720
and bring pain and
misfortune to people

00:04:13.720 --> 00:04:15.255
don't count as inventions!

00:04:16.990 --> 00:04:18.091
XEROSIC: What do you know?

00:04:19.126 --> 00:04:20.627
CLEMONT: Real inventions are

00:04:20.627 --> 00:04:21.495
things that help
people and Pokémon!

00:04:23.864 --> 00:04:25.298
XEROSIC: You think
that will change the world?

00:04:27.367 --> 00:04:29.002
CROBAT: [APPEARING]

00:04:29.002 --> 00:04:31.238
CLEMONT: I believe
it with all my heart!

00:04:31.238 --> 00:04:35.041
XEROSIC: All right, Crobat, use
Air Slash! Malamar, Psycho Cut!

00:04:35.041 --> 00:04:36.510
CROBAT: [AIR SLASH MOVE]
MALAMAR: [PSYCHO CUT MOVE]

00:04:38.011 --> 00:04:40.347
CLEMONT: Bunnelby, use Mud Shot!
Chespin, use Pin Missile!

00:04:52.926 --> 00:04:54.828
MABLE: It looks
like we have visitors.

00:04:54.828 --> 00:04:56.663
WEAVILE: [PLEASED]

00:04:56.663 --> 00:04:59.566
MEOWTH: Someone's there!
MABLE: Ice Shard, GO!

00:04:59.566 --> 00:05:00.567
WEAVILE: [ICE SHARD MOVE]

00:05:05.939 --> 00:05:07.741
SERENA: Braixen, ready?
BRAIXEN: [AFFIRMATIVE]

00:05:07.741 --> 00:05:10.343
MABLE: Weavile, use Ice Shard!

00:05:10.343 --> 00:05:12.245
WEAVILE: [ICE SHARD MOVE]
SERENA: Use Flamethrower!

00:05:12.245 --> 00:05:13.013
BRAIXEN: [FLAMETHROWER MOVE]

00:05:15.782 --> 00:05:17.918
MAIRIN: She's amazing...

00:05:17.918 --> 00:05:21.087
MABLE: Icy Wind, GO!
WEAVILE: [ICY WIND MOVE]

00:05:25.492 --> 00:05:27.194
WEAVILE: [PAINED]

00:05:27.194 --> 00:05:28.128
MABLE: What was that?!

00:05:29.062 --> 00:05:30.130
MAIRIN: Hey, look!

00:05:32.966 --> 00:05:33.433
MAIRIN: Steven!

00:05:34.534 --> 00:05:36.002
JESSIE:
You mean Steven the Champion?!

00:05:39.606 --> 00:05:41.374
STEVEN: Use Meteor Mash!

00:05:41.374 --> 00:05:42.776
MEGA METAGROSS:
[METEOR MASH MOVE]

00:05:43.577 --> 00:05:44.678
WEAVILE: [SCARED]

00:05:48.748 --> 00:05:50.083
MABLE:
The Hoenn Champion, Steven...

00:05:51.718 --> 00:05:54.120
STEVEN:
Lysandre fooled me, all right...

00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:56.523
STEVEN: But he fooled
the whole world, after all.

00:05:56.523 --> 00:05:59.292
MABLE: Oh please! Deception
has nothing to do with it.

00:05:59.292 --> 00:06:01.061
This is a great undertaking
to recreate the world!

00:06:02.829 --> 00:06:04.798
STEVEN: Great undertaking, huh?

00:06:04.798 --> 00:06:06.867
MABLE: The smart thing
to do would be to side with us.

00:06:10.170 --> 00:06:13.306
STEVEN: Really? You think so,
Battle me, and you're going to

00:06:13.306 --> 00:06:15.375
find out the hard
way that you're no match.

00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:16.376
MAIRIN: Steven!

00:06:17.944 --> 00:06:19.379
PROFESSOR SYCAMORE:
We're happy you're here!

00:06:19.379 --> 00:06:20.981
STEVEN: Well, I'm glad I
came to check on things before

00:06:20.981 --> 00:06:23.083
going to Prism Tower.

00:06:23.083 --> 00:06:24.651
PROFESSOR SYCAMORE:
Mairin's Chespin is inside...

00:06:24.651 --> 00:06:26.152
and the Giant Rock.

00:06:26.152 --> 00:06:28.054
STEVEN: Right.

00:06:28.054 --> 00:06:29.956
JAMES:
It really is the Hoenn Champion!

00:06:29.956 --> 00:06:31.291
JESSIE: Get that babe on tape!

00:06:31.291 --> 00:06:32.959
MEOWTH: Cool your jets.

00:06:32.959 --> 00:06:34.861
WOBBUFFET: [AFFIRMATIVE]

00:06:34.861 --> 00:06:36.696
STEVEN:
I'll handle this. Get Going!

00:06:36.696 --> 00:06:37.898
MAIRIN: Right!

00:06:42.102 --> 00:06:43.403
MABLE: Weavile, now, Ice Shard!

00:06:44.170 --> 00:06:45.805
WEAVILE: [ICE SHARD MOVE]

00:06:45.805 --> 00:06:46.940
TEAM FLARE GRUNT X 4:
Use Dark Pulse!

00:06:46.940 --> 00:06:47.707
HOUNDOOM X 2/SNEASEL :
[DARK PULSE MOVE]

00:06:47.707 --> 00:06:49.142
STEVEN: Use Flash Cannon!

00:06:49.142 --> 00:06:50.477
MEGA METAGROSS:
[FLASH CANNON MOVE]

00:06:52.779 --> 00:06:54.614
MAIRIN: This way!

00:06:54.614 --> 00:06:56.883
JESSIE: We are currently inside
the evil Team Flare's secret

00:06:56.883 --> 00:06:59.152
base, but we will
continue our coverage, even when

00:06:59.152 --> 00:07:00.587
faced with grave danger!

00:07:02.656 --> 00:07:03.924
DRAPION: [SLUDGE BOMB MOVE]

00:07:08.795 --> 00:07:09.763
SERENA: Are you all right?

00:07:10.997 --> 00:07:11.765
CELOSIA: Come on...

00:07:13.233 --> 00:07:15.502
CELOSIA: You need
prior approval for an interview.

00:07:15.502 --> 00:07:16.836
JESSIE: Why you...

00:07:16.836 --> 00:07:18.672
JAMES: Who do think you are?!

00:07:18.672 --> 00:07:20.106
MEOWTH: Your glasses
are choking your brain!

00:07:23.610 --> 00:07:25.712
SERENA: Team Rocket!

00:07:25.712 --> 00:07:27.013
CELOSIA: You keep
appearing like a bad dream.

00:07:28.014 --> 00:07:29.349
JESSIE: Now get going.

00:07:29.349 --> 00:07:30.550
JAMES: Go and save
your precious Pokémon.

00:07:33.186 --> 00:07:36.323
MEOWTH: Any enemy of
our enemy is a good buddy to us!

00:07:36.323 --> 00:07:38.258
JAMES: We have no
intention of handing this world

00:07:38.258 --> 00:07:40.160
over to you thugs.

00:07:40.160 --> 00:07:42.262
JESSIE: It's a
Team Rocket world. Wait...

00:07:42.262 --> 00:07:44.030
MEOWTH:
It's really the Boss's world!

00:07:44.030 --> 00:07:46.833
CELOSIA:
Stop the babble. It's so boring.

00:07:46.833 --> 00:07:49.536
JESSIE: I know you are.
Gourgeist, use Seed Bomb!

00:07:49.536 --> 00:07:50.637
JAMES: Inkay, use Psybeam!

00:07:52.105 --> 00:07:53.406
GOURGEIST: [APPEARING]
INKAY: [APPEARING]

00:07:53.406 --> 00:07:55.008
GOURGEIST: [SEED BOMB MOVE]

00:07:55.008 --> 00:07:57.410
CELOSIA: Drapion! Sludge Bomb!

00:07:57.410 --> 00:07:58.044
DRAPION: [SLUDGE BOMB MOVE]

00:07:59.946 --> 00:08:00.814
PROFESSOR SYCAMORE:
We'd better hurry!

00:08:03.783 --> 00:08:05.618
ALAIN: Thunder Punch, NOW!

00:08:05.618 --> 00:08:06.753
MEGA CHARIZARD:
[THUNDER PUNCH MOVE]

00:08:06.753 --> 00:08:08.455
MEGA GYARADOS: [PAINED]

00:08:08.455 --> 00:08:09.923
ASH: Dragon Pulse!

00:08:09.923 --> 00:08:11.791
GOODRA: [DRAGON PULSE MOVE]

00:08:12.692 --> 00:08:13.860
MEGA GYARADOS: [ANGRY]

00:08:13.860 --> 00:08:15.295
LYSANDRE: Use Hyper Beam!

00:08:15.295 --> 00:08:16.596
MEGA GYARADOS: [HYPER BEAM MOVE]

00:08:20.133 --> 00:08:21.768
GOODRA: [STUNNED]

00:08:23.336 --> 00:08:25.138
ASH: All right, Goodra, return!

00:08:27.540 --> 00:08:29.709
LYSANDRE: Oh, done so soon?

00:08:29.709 --> 00:08:32.846
ASH: No way!
I never quit until it's over!

00:08:34.581 --> 00:08:37.417
ASH: I think you called that
fighting spirit. But there's a

00:08:37.417 --> 00:08:39.686
lot more to a
Pokémon's strength than that!

00:08:39.686 --> 00:08:42.922
ASH: I learned that on my
journey. My Pokémon's strength

00:08:42.922 --> 00:08:45.458
and my strength come from
believing in each other and

00:08:45.458 --> 00:08:47.327
caring for each
other more than anything else.

00:08:53.066 --> 00:08:54.634
ASH: And if you don't
understand that, we'll show you!

00:08:56.202 --> 00:08:58.171
ASH: Talonflame,
now! Use Flame Charge!

00:08:58.171 --> 00:08:59.406
And Greninja, you use Cut!

00:09:00.840 --> 00:09:01.975
GRENINJA: [CUT MOVE]
TALONFLAME: [FLAME CHARGE MOVE]

00:09:01.975 --> 00:09:04.010
LYSANDRE: Use Stone Edge!

00:09:04.010 --> 00:09:06.046
MEGA GYARADOS: [STONE EDGE MOVE]
TALONFLAME: [PAINED]

00:09:06.046 --> 00:09:08.048
ALAIN: Catch them!

00:09:08.048 --> 00:09:09.949
MEGA CHARIZARD: [AFFIRMATIVE]
MEGA CHARIZARD: [EXERTION]

00:09:09.949 --> 00:09:11.418
MEGA GYARADOS: [ROARING]

00:09:11.418 --> 00:09:13.086
ALAIN: Above you!
LYSANDRE: Dragon Tail!

00:09:13.086 --> 00:09:14.320
MEGA GYARADOS:
[DRAGON TAIL MOVE]

00:09:15.755 --> 00:09:18.691
GRENINJA /MEGA CHARIZARD:
[PAINED]

00:09:18.691 --> 00:09:21.895
GRENINJA /MEGA CHARIZARD:
[EXERTION] TALONFLAME: [STUNNED]

00:09:21.895 --> 00:09:22.796
ASH: You were great.
Thanks, Talonflame.

00:09:24.898 --> 00:09:25.899
PIKACHU: [CONCERNED]

00:09:28.968 --> 00:09:29.602
LYSANDRE: What's wrong?

00:09:31.104 --> 00:09:33.606
LYSANDRE: Ash, with all that big
talk of yours, is that all you

00:09:33.606 --> 00:09:36.876
can come up with? Well then,
this is it! Use Hyper Beam!

00:09:36.876 --> 00:09:38.344
MEGA GYARADOS: [HYPER BEAM MOVE]

00:09:44.851 --> 00:09:46.886
ASH: Hey, you're...

00:09:46.886 --> 00:09:48.221
ALAIN: Malva!
MEGA HOUNDOOM: [EXERTION]

00:09:48.221 --> 00:09:50.590
MALVA: Time for all
this to end. Right now!

00:09:50.590 --> 00:09:52.225
LYSANDRE: Malva...What
is the meaning of this?

00:09:53.159 --> 00:09:55.095
MALVA: It's really simple.

00:09:55.095 --> 00:09:56.729
I'm putting my
complete trust in these kids.

00:09:59.799 --> 00:10:00.767
ASH/SERENA/CLEMONT/BONNIE:
"Who's that Pokémon?"

00:10:06.239 --> 00:10:07.674
ASH/SERENA/CLEMONT/BONNIE:
"It's Crobat!"

00:10:15.215 --> 00:10:17.684
MALVA: I know this world is
hardly perfect. Far from it.

00:10:19.853 --> 00:10:20.687
LYSANDRE: Then why
are you getting in my way?

00:10:22.188 --> 00:10:25.024
MALVA: Because I saw them!

00:10:25.024 --> 00:10:28.161
MALVA: Changing the world isn't
about destroying it! And people

00:10:28.161 --> 00:10:29.062
like them are proof of that!

00:10:30.830 --> 00:10:33.933
LYSANDRE: Then let me ask you.
These children, who are destined

00:10:33.933 --> 00:10:36.603
to lose... what kind of world
are they capable of making?

00:10:38.338 --> 00:10:39.706
MALVA: They
haven't lost yet, have they?

00:10:42.242 --> 00:10:44.544
MALVA: Changing the world
is not something they can do by

00:10:44.544 --> 00:10:47.714
themselves, but if adults
like us offer to lend a hand,

00:10:47.714 --> 00:10:50.016
then I'm sure things
can change for the better.

00:10:50.016 --> 00:10:52.018
MALVA: The possibilities are
real, and I want to see them!

00:10:54.888 --> 00:10:58.324
LYSANDRE: Our conversation is
through. You've wasted enough of

00:10:58.324 --> 00:11:01.427
my precious time!
Gyarados, Incinerate, NOW!

00:11:02.228 --> 00:11:03.396
MEGA GYARADOS: [INCINERATE MOVE]

00:11:04.230 --> 00:11:06.766
ASH: Greninja! Water Shuriken!

00:11:06.766 --> 00:11:08.801
GRENINJA: [WATER SHURIKEN MOVE]

00:11:14.507 --> 00:11:17.177
ASH: Now look! You may not
like this world much. So what?

00:11:18.545 --> 00:11:20.513
It belongs to people
and Pokémon...Everyone!

00:11:22.415 --> 00:11:24.951
ASH: Your plan to recreate
the world...All that talk...

00:11:24.951 --> 00:11:26.452
You have no
right to say any of that!

00:11:28.922 --> 00:11:30.657
ASH: There are people
meeting new people all the time!

00:11:31.891 --> 00:11:33.126
ASH: People making
their dreams come true...

00:11:34.561 --> 00:11:35.728
ASH: People just getting
started on their journeys!

00:11:37.297 --> 00:11:38.464
ASH: People who are
healing from old wounds...

00:11:39.732 --> 00:11:40.934
ASH: Everyone's
got their own tomorrow!

00:11:42.368 --> 00:11:43.937
ASH: And you have no right to

00:11:43.937 --> 00:11:45.238
take their
tomorrows away from them!

00:11:46.372 --> 00:11:48.641
ASH: That's why we fight.

00:11:48.641 --> 00:11:50.843
My Pokémon and I are
fighting for their tomorrows!

00:11:50.843 --> 00:11:52.345
PIKACHU: [DEFIANT]

00:11:54.180 --> 00:11:55.415
MALVA: Sounds like the future

00:11:55.415 --> 00:11:56.482
Ash talks
about is pretty bright.

00:12:00.620 --> 00:12:04.591
LYSANDRE: How naive can you get?
You sound just like me back

00:12:04.591 --> 00:12:05.959
in the days when I was naive!

00:12:08.928 --> 00:12:10.330
MAIRIN: Thank goodness!
Chespie's safe.

00:12:11.798 --> 00:12:12.632
PROFESSOR SYCAMORE: Let's
take Chespie back to my lab.

00:12:13.533 --> 00:12:15.568
MAIRIN: Thanks, Professor.

00:12:15.568 --> 00:12:17.103
BRAIXEN: [FLAMETHROWER MOVE]
PANCHAM: [STONE EDGE MOVE]

00:12:17.103 --> 00:12:18.438
SYLVEON: [FAIRY WIND MOVE]

00:12:22.475 --> 00:12:24.143
SERENA: They don't give up!

00:12:24.143 --> 00:12:25.545
SERENA: How's Chespie?

00:12:25.545 --> 00:12:26.512
MAIRIN: It's fine. See?

00:12:28.481 --> 00:12:30.416
SERENA: Thank goodness!

00:12:30.416 --> 00:12:31.117
PROFESSOR SYCAMORE:
Now, how do we get ourselves

00:12:31.117 --> 00:12:32.318
out of this situation?

00:12:37.257 --> 00:12:38.358
STEVEN: Now, come on...

00:12:39.859 --> 00:12:41.527
You don't really want to
get hurt, do you?

00:12:41.527 --> 00:12:42.295
MAIRIN: It's Steven!

00:12:49.435 --> 00:12:50.403
BONNIE: Thanks, Blaziken!

00:12:51.204 --> 00:12:52.405
ZYGARDE 50%: [SNARLING]

00:12:53.473 --> 00:12:54.907
BONNIE: Squishy...

00:12:54.907 --> 00:12:56.943
BLAZIKEN MASK:
Are you sure about this?

00:12:56.943 --> 00:12:59.045
BONNIE: I know Squishy will
understand! Please believe me!

00:13:00.413 --> 00:13:03.182
BONNIE: Squishy! It's fine now!

00:13:03.182 --> 00:13:06.319
BONNIE:
It's me! Bonnie! Can you see me?

00:13:06.319 --> 00:13:08.588
BONNIE: Squishy, you
don't want to do this, do you?

00:13:09.222 --> 00:13:10.256
I know you don't!

00:13:11.157 --> 00:13:13.026
ZYGARDE 50%: [ROARING]

00:13:15.895 --> 00:13:17.230
BONNIE: No! Blaziken Mask!

00:13:20.233 --> 00:13:21.000
BONNIE: Squishy...

00:13:30.209 --> 00:13:36.282
BONNIE: Squishy...
Squishy...You're oh‐so‐very

00:13:36.282 --> 00:13:40.720
soft...Squishy...Squishy...

00:13:42.555 --> 00:13:47.927
BONNIE: You're oh‐so‐pretty
green... Squishy...Squishy...

00:13:50.430 --> 00:13:55.101
the cutest I've ever
seen...You're happy sleeping

00:13:55.101 --> 00:13:58.004
in my bag. Squishy...

00:14:04.744 --> 00:14:07.580
ZYGARDE 50%: [GROWLING]

00:14:07.580 --> 00:14:09.449
BONNIE: Squishy...Squishy...

00:14:10.950 --> 00:14:15.021
You're oh‐so‐very
soft...Squishy...Squishy...

00:14:16.089 --> 00:14:18.091
You're oh‐so‐pretty green...

00:14:20.259 --> 00:14:24.263
BONNIE: Squishy, Squishy...
The cutest I've ever seen...

00:14:25.832 --> 00:14:29.402
You're happy sleeping
in my bag Squishy...

00:14:31.270 --> 00:14:34.507
How I wish I understood
where you come from...

00:14:36.609 --> 00:14:40.146
BONNIE: And the way you get
all your food from the sun...

00:14:41.681 --> 00:14:47.653
Mysterious Squishy, how I
love you. So, oh please,

00:14:47.653 --> 00:14:49.956
won't you please,
tell me some more!

00:14:51.624 --> 00:14:57.163
Squishy and me,
nuzzling cheeks.

00:14:57.163 --> 00:15:00.867
BONNIE: Best friends forever,
we're so happy...

00:15:02.135 --> 00:15:07.039
I promise I'll never leave,
Squishy...

00:15:07.039 --> 00:15:10.643
My little Squishy, here's
my song for you...

00:15:12.478 --> 00:15:17.116
I'll never leave Squishy...
My sweet Squishy, that's you!

00:15:41.607 --> 00:15:43.509
BONNIE: Squishy...

00:15:43.509 --> 00:15:47.780
BONNIE: You
heard me. You heard my voice!

00:15:56.055 --> 00:15:57.256
BONNIE: Squishy!
DEDENNE: [JOYFUL]

00:16:09.802 --> 00:16:11.270
ASH: What's happening?

00:16:11.270 --> 00:16:12.738
MALVA:
Amazing. Zygarde's splitting!

00:16:13.873 --> 00:16:14.907
LYSANDRE:
What's going on, Xerosic?!

00:16:16.242 --> 00:16:18.144
XEROSIC: Look,
I'm too busy to deal with that!

00:16:18.144 --> 00:16:19.011
I'm battling an intruder!

00:16:20.112 --> 00:16:21.113
LYSANDRE: Battling an intruder?

00:16:22.415 --> 00:16:24.183
XEROSIC:
It's the Lumiose Gym Leader!

00:16:24.183 --> 00:16:26.052
ASH: Clemont!

00:16:26.052 --> 00:16:27.386
LYSANDRE:
You're all so useless...

00:16:39.499 --> 00:16:41.000
SQUISHY: [EXHAUSTED]

00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:43.302
BONNIE:
Squishy... You're okay now...

00:16:43.302 --> 00:16:44.337
SQUISHY: [PEACEFUL]

00:16:48.107 --> 00:16:51.310
CLEMONT: Chespin, use Pin
Missile! Bunnelby, Mud Shot!

00:16:51.310 --> 00:16:54.814
CHESPIN: [PIN MISSILE MOVE]
BUNNELBY: [MUD SHOT MOVE]

00:16:54.814 --> 00:16:56.282
MALAMAR : [PAINED]
CROBAT: [PAINED]

00:16:57.750 --> 00:16:59.752
XEROSIC: Return, you two!

00:17:01.787 --> 00:17:04.190
XEROSIC: Now what?

00:17:04.190 --> 00:17:06.592
CLEMBOT: I've done it!
I've infiltrated the system!

00:17:06.592 --> 00:17:07.960
XEROSIC: What are you doing?!

00:17:07.960 --> 00:17:09.362
CLEMONT: Activate the system!

00:17:09.362 --> 00:17:10.463
CLEMBOT: Roger!

00:17:16.235 --> 00:17:17.203
CLEMBOT:
That worked out quite nicely.

00:17:18.671 --> 00:17:19.872
CLEMONT: Who knew?
It sure came in handy, though.

00:17:21.107 --> 00:17:22.208
CLEMBOT:
It's my invention, after all.

00:17:25.444 --> 00:17:26.979
CLEMONT: Synchronizing
you with the system.

00:17:26.979 --> 00:17:28.147
Shutting it all down!

00:17:30.049 --> 00:17:31.183
CLEMONT: Hold on. What?

00:17:32.652 --> 00:17:35.621
CLEMBOT: If we force it to shut
down, it will heavily stress the

00:17:35.621 --> 00:17:38.491
system. And because I'm
currently synchronized with it,

00:17:38.491 --> 00:17:40.960
my main memory will be
completely erased. I won't

00:17:40.960 --> 00:17:42.929
remember a thing.

00:17:42.929 --> 00:17:45.097
CLEMONT: Nothing?
CLEMBOT: Right!

00:17:45.097 --> 00:17:47.033
CLEMONT: Hold on a minute!
I can't do that!

00:17:49.035 --> 00:17:50.570
CLEMBOT: But, if we don't,
this crisis will never end.

00:17:53.706 --> 00:17:55.975
CLEMBOT: You're Clemont.
The Leader of the Lumiose Gym.

00:17:57.376 --> 00:17:59.045
A kind and generous Gym Leader.

00:18:00.846 --> 00:18:03.115
CLEMBOT: Always thinking of
others. Considering the good of

00:18:03.115 --> 00:18:04.350
the many over the one.

00:18:06.719 --> 00:18:08.921
CLEMBOT: You know
what you must do. So do it!

00:18:18.598 --> 00:18:20.132
CLEMONT: I know. I know!

00:18:21.968 --> 00:18:25.738
CLEMONT: I have to! Or
I won't be able to help anyone!

00:18:42.088 --> 00:18:45.124
CLEMBOT: You are the one who
can save the world. You once

00:18:45.124 --> 00:18:46.926
suggested to me
that we learn together.

00:18:49.695 --> 00:18:51.430
CLEMONT: And I want to keep
on learning! Right, Clembot?

00:18:52.932 --> 00:18:54.133
CLEMBOT: Well put, sir.

00:18:55.768 --> 00:18:58.170
CLEMBOT:
It made me happy. Thank you.

00:19:00.673 --> 00:19:03.976
CLEMONT: Oh, Clembot...
I'm so glad I know you!

00:19:05.811 --> 00:19:07.880
CLEMBOT: Thanks. And I'm
so glad that you created me.

00:19:08.814 --> 00:19:10.016
You're brilliant!

00:19:11.050 --> 00:19:12.151
CLEMONT: Clembot...

00:19:51.290 --> 00:19:52.658
SQUISHY: [STARTLED]

00:19:52.658 --> 00:19:53.959
BONNIE: What's wrong?

00:19:53.959 --> 00:19:55.461
SQUISHY: [EXCITED]

00:19:59.699 --> 00:20:01.100
CHESPIN/BUNNELBY: [SAD]

00:20:13.145 --> 00:20:14.580
MALVA: There. The other
one has been freed, too.

00:20:16.082 --> 00:20:18.484
ALAIN: Did Clemont do that?

00:20:18.484 --> 00:20:22.121
ASH: I bet! Lysandre!
You guys just lost big time!

00:20:22.121 --> 00:20:24.623
PIKACHU: [TRIUMPHANT]

00:20:24.623 --> 00:20:27.226
LYSANDRE: I have to say there
seems to be no limit to how much

00:20:27.226 --> 00:20:28.527
you fools can entertain me.

00:20:29.195 --> 00:20:31.530
MEGA GYARADOS: [ROARING]

00:20:36.268 --> 00:20:38.504
NARRATOR: Zygarde is finally
free from Team Flare's control,

00:20:40.039 --> 00:20:43.275
thanks to Clemont and Bonnie.
But will Ash and Alain be able

00:20:43.275 --> 00:20:47.012
to protect the world and its
future from Lysandre? The Team

00:20:47.012 --> 00:20:50.382
Flare incident that shook
Kalos takes an unexpected turn,

00:20:50.382 --> 00:20:52.451
as the journey continues!

